        "text": "Hey guys,\n\nI have been using javaScript a lot in Unity to make games and I am a little bit newer to javaScript in Web Development. I am trying to make a form to collect information and add it to an existing object. any feed back would be helpful. Here is what I have so far.\n\n.js file_________________________\n\ndata = [ { name: \"Mark-Paul Gosselaar\", photo_url: \"\" }, { name: \"Delta Burke\", photo_url: \"img/avatars/delta.png\" }, { name: \"Alf\", photo_url: \"img/avatars/alf.png\" }, { name: \"Jaleel White\", photo_url: \"img/avatars/jaleel.png\" }, { name: \"Ralph Macchio\", photo_url: \"img/avatars/ralph.png\" }, { name: \"Candace Cameron\", photo_url: \"img/avatars/candace.png\" }, { name: \"Patrick Duffy\", photo_url: \"img/avatars/pduff.png\" }, { name: \"Arnold Schwartzengger\", photo_url: \"img/avatars/arnold.png\" } ];\n\nIndex page___________\n\n<!DOCTYPE html> <html> <head> <link href=\"css/application.css\" rel=\"stylesheet\"> <script src=\"js/vendor/jquery.min.js\" type=\"text/javascript\"></script> <script src=\"js/vendor/underscore.js\" type=\"text/javascript\"></script> <script src=\"js/application.js\" type=\"text/javascript\"></script> </head> <body> <div id=\"main-content\"> <!-- The page width is 817px --> <!-- Example of using the form CSS to help you out. --> <form> <div> <label>Full Name</label> <input name=\"name\" type=\"text\" required /> </div> <div> <label>Photo URL</label> <input name=\"photo_url\" /> </div> <button type=\"submit\">Create</button> </form> <hr /> <!-- Employee list goes here. There is initial data for you in application.js --> <script> $( document ).ready(function() { var html = \"\"; for( i=0; i<data.length; i++ ) { //create the image div html = \"<div id=\\\"image_container\" + i + \"\\\"><img src=\\\"\" + data[i].photo_url + \"\\\"></div>\"; //create the name div html += \"<div id=\\\"inner_container\" + i + \"\\\">\" + data[i].name + \"</div>\"; //append the divs to the body $(\"body\").append(html); //add click event to each image div $(\"#image_container\"+i).click(function() { alert( $(this).attr('id') ); }); } }); $('.myElementClass').css('text-align','center'); </script> </div> </body> </html>\n\nok… One thing I wasnt sure of, based on your code was the click event on generated images… do you want to make them clickable?\n\nbut here’s what I came up with… I created a fiddle for ya too.\n\nEDIT: also, in your Data Array, your values were quoted, but your names were not.\n\nHTML: Notice I added a “#results”\n\nto hold the data.\n\n<div id=\"main-content\"> <!-- The page width is 817px --> <!-- Example of using the form CSS to help you out. --> <form> <div> <label>Full Name</label> <input name=\"name\" type=\"text\" required /> </div> <div> <label>Photo URL</label> <input name=\"photo_url\" /> </div> <button id=\"create\" type=\"submit\">Create</button> </form> </div> <hr> <h4> Results:</h4> <div id=\"results\"></div>\n\nJS:\n\nvar data = [ {\"name\": \"Delta Burke\", \"photo_url\": \"img/avatars/delta.png\"}, {\"name\": \"Alf\", \"photo_url\": \"img/avatars/alf.png\"}, {\"name\": \"Jaleel White\", \"photo_url\": \"img/avatars/jaleel.png\"}, {\"name\": \"Ralph Macchio\", \"photo_url\": \"img/avatars/ralph.png\"} ]; // function to JSONify the form data so it can be pushed into the data array, //then re-calling the \"displayNewEntry' function, passing the newly updated data array function serializeObject(obj){ var o = {}; var a = $(obj).serializeArray(); $.each(a, function() { if (o[this.name] !== undefined) { if (!o[this.name].push) { o[this.name] = [o[this.name]]; } o[this.name].push(this.value || ''); } else { o[this.name] = this.value || ''; } }); data.push(o); displayNewEntry(data); } //function to append data array values to the '#results' element function displayNewEntry(array) { $('#results').html(''); console.log(array); $.each(array, function (index, value) { $('<div>').append(value.name).append($('<img>').attr('src', value.photo_url)).appendTo($('#results')); }); } //calling the displayNewEntry function and passing the data array displayNewEntry(data); // calling the serialize function, on Submit $(\"form\").on(\"submit\", function (event) { event.preventDefault(); serializeObject('form'); });\n\nThis worked really well, the problem is that I want it to style everything like i have in my original code and have the delete buttons that are horribly hard coded in. lol I am trying to modify this part of your code so that it only populates the newly added entries.\n\n//function to append data array values to the '#results' element function displayNewEntry(array) { $('#results').html(''); console.log(array); $.each(array, function (index, value) { $('<div>').append(value.name).append($('<img>').attr('src', value.photo_url)).appendTo($('#results')); }); }\n\nPerhaps there is a way to make my code simply add the data to the array like in your function. I have been trying to figure that out, but it seems I am having issues grasping your code.\n\nnote: Also that onlclick alert function before was just my beginning of making the delete buttons.\n\n<script type=\"text/javascript\"> $( document ).ready(function() { var html = \"\"; for( i=0; i<data.length; i++ ) { //create the image div html = \"<div id=\\\"image_container\" + i + \"\\\"><img src=\\\"\" + data[i].photo_url + \"\\\"></div>\"; //create the name div html += \"<div id=\\\"inner_container\" + i + \"\\\">\" + \"<h2>\" + data[i].name + \"</h2>\" + \"<button id=\\\"button_delete\" + i + \"\\\">X</button>\" + \"</div>\"; //append the divs to the body $(\"body\").append(html); //add deletion button 0 $(\"#button_delete0\").click(function() { $(\"div\").remove(\"#inner_container0\"); $(\"div\").remove(\"#image_container0\"); }); //add deletion button 1 $(\"#button_delete1\").click(function() { $(\"div\").remove(\"#inner_container1\"); $(\"div\").remove(\"#image_container1\"); }); //add deletion button 2 $(\"#button_delete2\").click(function() { $(\"div\").remov